            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "seems like vterm `erase_internal`  fills blank cells with the current screen->pen.bg (green) instead of the default background color. so this can aslo reproduce on vim or emacs(?).  this can fix ... ðŸ¤”\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/vterm/screen.c b/src/nvim/vterm/screen.c\nindex c7bf0141b4..ff4edd734c 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/vterm/screen.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/vterm/screen.c\n@@ -234,8 +234,8 @@ static int erase_internal(VTermRect rect, int selective, void *user)\n       cell->schar = 0;\n       cell->pen = (ScreenPen){\n         // Only copy .fg and .bg; leave things like rv in reset state\n-        .fg = screen->pen.fg,\n-        .bg = screen->pen.bg,\n+        .fg = screen->state->default_fg,\n+        .bg = screen->state->default_bg,\n       };\n       cell->pen.dwl = info->doublewidth;\n       cell->pen.dhl = info->doubleheight;\n```",
            "created_at": "2025-10-07T08:00:34Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/10922#issuecomment-3375651044",
